revision.text: ==English== ===Alternative forms=== * {{l|en|xynistery}} * {{l|en|xinisteri}} ===Etymology=== {{uder|en|el|ξυνιστέρι|sc=Grek}}. ===Noun=== {{en-noun|-}} # A white [[grape]] indigenous to the island of [[Cyprus]]. #* {{quote-journal|en|2009|January 24|Gord Stimmell|Greece, France, Australia shine in this release|Toronto Star|url=http://www.thestar.com/living/article/574263 |passage=This crisp, lemony white is made using '''xynisteri''' grapes, imported centuries before from the Greek mainland.}} ====Synonyms==== * xynisteri grape [[Category:en:Fruits]] [[Category:en:Grapevines]]
